And  user fills Guarantor field with valid data

And  user check Form of Instrument (22E) radio-button with value DIRECT
And  user fills Type of Guarantee (22K) field with valid data
And  user fills Wording of Guarantee (22J) field with valid data
And  user fills Nominal Amount & Currency (39P) field with valid data
And  user fills Applicable Rules (40C) field with valid data
And  user check Validity (23B) radio-button with value LIMITED
And  user fills Expiry Date (31L) field with tomorrow date
And  user fills Reference Type field with valid data
And  user check Delivery Type radio-button with value DIGITAL GUARANTEE
And  user fills GVP Delivery field with valid data
And  APPLICANT click on [SAVE] button from Guarantee Input Page
And  APPLICANT click on [YES] button from Guarantee Registration Popup
And  System sets Guarantee status to DRAFT
And  Guarantee status font color is GRAY
And  APPLICANT click [EDIT] button from Guarantee View Page
And  user fills Instrument Purpose (26D) field with valid data
And  APPLICANT click [SAVE] button from Guarantee View Page
And  Assigns Guarantee request a unique id
And  System sets Guarantee status to NEW
And  Guarantee status font color is PURPLE
And  system loads Guarantee Request View Page
And  Guarantee data matches with default mandatory values from Guarantee Input Page
